ublic\n\u201cPORTSMOUTH'S LARGEST EXCLUSIVE STORE FOR WOMEN AND CHILDREN\u201d\nThe A.tlas Company\n307-09 ChlUlcothe St. PORTSMOUTH, OHIO\nA NEW ERA in the progress and merchandising history of\nThe Atlas Company, marked with a store-wide Fashion Sale\nthat bids fair to eclipse all former records.\nThe Atlas Co.\n$50,000.00\nJanuary\nClearance\nMammoth 15-Day Clearaway Involving Thousands of\nDollars Worth of Fine Apparel at Low Sale Prices.\nII\nWORTH COMING MILES!\nThis sale will include ALL GOATS, reduced to the last degree\nof lowness\u2014hundreds of DRESSES, in many instances below\ntheir actual cost\u2014more than a thousand pairs of smart SHOES\n\u2014all CHILDREN\u2019S GOATS and FROCKS\u2014hundreds of\npieces of fine UNDERTHINGS, SILK HOSIERY and MIS\nCELLANEOUS ITEMS\u2014$50,000.00 worth of fashionable wear\ning apparel at prices that will enable you to save many, many\ndollars.\n\nStarts Thursday, Jan. 9th and Continues for 15 Selling\nDays or While Stock Lasts.\nv\nSMjSgESM^IW^a\u00abi^lKM\u00abSS>iSlBlKlKi!d\nAUCTIONEER\nI have authorized H.\nM. McCreight to book\na Sales for me. Parties\njjj desiring our service\nplease Call Mr. Homer\nMcCreight, Seaman Ex.\n1 Seaman, hio.\nI O. O. ROLFE\nBELFAST, OHIO\nNotice to Contractors\nSTATE OF OHIO. DEPARTMENT\nHIGHWAYS\nOF\nColumbus, Ohio, January 3, 1930.\nUNIT PRICE CONTRACT\nSealed proposals will be received at the\noffice of the State Highway Director at Col\numbus, Ohio, until two o\u2019clock p. m.. Eastern\nStandard Time. Tuesday, January 2H, 1930, for\nimprovements in\nAdams County on Sections \u201cA-2,\u201d \u201cB\u201d and\n\u201cC\u201d of the Portsmouth-Cineinnati Road, S. H.\nNo. 119, State Route No. 125. by furnishing\nand erecting 10,040 lin. ft. of guard rail.\nEstimated cost, $0,731.00.\nDate set for completion, July 1. 1930.\nThe bidder must submit with his bid a cer\ntified check in an amount equal to five per\ncent (5) of the estimated cost, but in no\nevent more than ten thousand dollars ($1.0,\n000.00.)\nSpecifications are on file in the office of\nthe County Surveyor, Resident Engineer and\nthe Department of Highways.\nThe Director reserves the right to reject\nany and all bids.\nROBERT N. WAID\nState Highway Director.\nl-9-2t.\nReport of the Condition\n\u2014OF THE\u2014\nWINCHESTER BANK CO.\nWINCHESTER, OHIO\nAt the clone of Business December 31, 1920.\nRESOURCES\nLoans .$205,575.73\nOverdrafts. 19.55\nState. County and Municipal Bonds 14,990.00\nOther Bonds, Stocks and Securities 80,003.05\nBanking House and Lot. 3,837.31\nFurniture and Fixtures 5,160.41\nReal Estate other than Banking....\nHouse 3,000.00\nDue from Reserve Banks and cash\nin vault 82,039.68\nTOTAL .$394,625.73\nLIABILITIES\nCapital Stock paid in 25,000.00\nSurplus Fund 30,000.00\nUndivided Profits less expenses, in\nterest and taxes paid 17,871.24\nIndividual Deposits subject to check 185,500.88\nDividends Unpaid 2,500.00\nSavings Deposits 133,751 .61\nTOTAL .\u2018.$394,625.73\nI, D. J. Corboy. Cashier of the above j\nnamed Winchester Bank Co., do solemnly\nswear that the above statement is true to the\nbest of my knowledge and belief.\nD. J. CORBOY, Cashier.\nCorrect \u2014attest:\nC. L. Fenton\nKirk Short\nW. C. Neu\nDirectors.\nState of Ohio, County of Adams.\nSubscribed and sworn to before me this\n6th day of January. 1930.\nI lSeal 1 W. C. N^v'L, Notary Public.\nRead Our Classified Advertisements.\nYEARS OF\nSERVICE\nHaving spent many years in this one section\u2014as did our fathers\nand forefathers before us\u2014Our foremost desire for the past eighty\none years has always been to render every possible service to the\nfamily in their hours of sorrow.\nWith this thought in mind we have always kept our Funeral Home\nand its equipment up-to-date, for it is only by so doing that we are\nable to truly serve.\nThe LAFFERTY FUNERAL HOME\nSince 1848\nPhone 159 West Union, Ohio\nBRANCH OFFICE\u2014 CHERRY FORK, O.\nChas. C.ustin, Manager\nV V V VWW %TV WV V V V %*W\nC. H. Newman, C. D. Asbury R. C. Bratton\nH. M. Walker M. C. Colliver\nSELLYOURTOBACCO\nAT THE\nWAREHOUSE\nBANK STREET PHONE 869\nMaysville, Kentucky\nNONE BETTER\nL. H. Smoot, Book-keeper Orville Fields, Floor Mgr.\nB. E. McClure, Auctioneer","height":"29088","width":"21924"}}
